•	Ability to identify opportunities and bring innovations to the business
•	Friendly yet strong personality with the ability to handle diplomatically adverse situations
•	Ability to lead, guide and interact with a persified group of stakeholders
•	Strong influencing and communication skills
Job DescriptionMy client is one of the world's leading energy companies, with over 60,000 employees around the world. Their operations includes production and transport of crude oil and natural gas; refining, marketing and distribution of fuels and related products; manufacturing and selling petrochemicals; generating power; and developing alternative energy resources for the future, including biofuels and geothermal energy.
RESPONSIBILITIES
•	Establish strategies with cross functional teams, identify opportunities to increase profitability (e.g. contracting strategies, new alliances, increase sharing mechanisms)
•	Interact with various parties to develop market intelligence of relevant commodity/services
•	Guides the Procurement team and stakeholders through the development of business case for change, alternative strategies and solutions
•	Develops and supports implementation plans working closely with stakeholders
•	Understands the Business drivers & imperatives in the area of safety, reliability, performance & cost effectiveness to drive value propositionsType:
